The Bee Reactor Adapter repo publishes two independent packages:

| Package | npm | Role |
|---------|-----|------|
| `packages/adapter` | `@liberuum-org/bee-reactor-adapter` | Core adapter: SwarmClient, SwarmChannel, ACT-encrypted sharing, PSS/GSOC chat, postage stamps |
| `packages/connect` | `@liberuum-org/connect` | Fork of Powerhouse Connect with Swarm landing page, settings UI, and chat panel |

Example integration into any Powerhouse project:

```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "@liberuum-org/bee-reactor-adapter": "0.23.0"
  },
  "overrides": {
    "@powerhousedao/connect": "npm:@liberuum-org/connect@6.0.0-dev.174-swarm.1"
  }
}
```

Each package publishes independently with `npm publish --otp=CODE` (the connect fork uses `--tag swarm`). Builds are driven by `npx tsc` for the adapter and `bun run build` for connect.
